laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Blood test for hemoglobin and lead
Complete blood count and differential count

laboratory_examinations.findings: Focal narrowing of a short segment of the distal thoracic esophagus; delayed passage of contrast material beyond this narrowing; intraesophageal reflux observed proximal to the narrowing; poststenotic dilatation distal to the narrowing.
Stenosis encountered 18 cm from the incisors; mucosa normal in this area. Stricture measured approximately 1 cm in length.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Mild improvement in the stricture observed after dilation with an 8-mm balloon.
